<doc id="677719" wikidata="Q7209058" url="?curid=677719" title="Polar Wrocław">
<text>Zakładowy Klub Sportowy Polar Wrocław, known simply as Polar Wrocław, is a Polish sports club based in the Zakrzów district of Wrocław, named after the local electronics company &quot;Polar&quot;. The women&#x27;s field hockey team existed since 1967. The men&#x27;s football team is currently competing in the amateur divisions. After being in the centre of a huge corruption scandal in 2004, the club was dissolved. On 11 March 2005, the club &quot;MKS Polar Wrocław-Zawidawie&quot; was founded which continued the club&#x27;s traditions until its disestablishment in 2015. In 2024, Polar was re-activated under its historic name.

==Current squad==
&quot;As of 8 April 2015&quot;














== Honours ==
*Polish Cup quarter-finalists: 2002–03
*9th place in II liga: 1999–2000, 2001–02

